    "body": "I have a screen recording here of it not working. Then I load a clean shell (same term emulator, tmux on, just zsh without the .zshrc, so that starfish does not load)\n\n\nNot working example:\n[![asciicast](https://asciinema.org/a/XqcHHAZzQ8U72s3Z31OWSrJ7D.svg)](https://asciinema.org/a/XqcHHAZzQ8U72s3Z31OWSrJ7D)\n\nWorking example:\n[![asciicast](https://asciinema.org/a/yZ7fBl3XOOatpFLIck4lSP5LS.svg)](https://asciinema.org/a/yZ7fBl3XOOatpFLIck4lSP5LS)\n\nNote:\nDon't mind the colors. Asciinema broke them. Also in the first example there is a `nc` typed after the actual nc command. Also the `~` after the first ctrl-c is not actually there. Again probably an artifact by asciinema. If I play the recordings on my laptop they look exactly like they would when I do the two examples for real.\n\n\nPS. I also tried installing starship from scratch ",
